It replaces and improves upon the functionality of the standard AutoIt pixel search functions, PixelGetColor and PixelSearch, allowing for more complex searches to be performed at much faster speeds.  It consists of a .dll file that contains the pixel searching logic, and an AutoIt wrapper file, which acts as an interface between your AutoIt script and the DLL. To start using FastFind, simply copy the files into the same folder as your script, and insert #include "FastFind.au3" near the top of your script file.
